  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/festive-blt-with-cheesy-garlic-baked-wedges/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a baking tray with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until the wedges have softened and are starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/festive-blt-with-cheesy-garlic-baked-wedges/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a separate baking tray with <strong>tin foil </strong>(to avoid mess!) and add your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/festive-blt-with-cheesy-garlic-baked-wedges/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the bacon and wedges are cooking, cut half your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>tomato[es]</strong> into slices</p><p>Dice the<strong> remaining tomato[es] </strong>finely</p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper and shred roughly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/festive-blt-with-cheesy-garlic-baked-wedges/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>mayo</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cranberry sauce </strong>and a good grind of <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>cranberry mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/festive-blt-with-cheesy-garlic-baked-wedges/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chips are done, transfer them to one side of the tray and top with <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>ciabattas </strong>to the other side and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until they're warmed through and the cheese has melted</p><p>Carefully slice the <strong>warmed ciabattas</strong> in half before serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/festive-blt-with-cheesy-garlic-baked-wedges/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Loosen your <strong>onion marmalade </strong>with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/festive-blt-with-cheesy-garlic-baked-wedges/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build, spread the <strong>cranberry mayo </strong>evenly between the <strong>ciabatta bases</strong> and top with your <strong>crispy onions</strong>, <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>bacon</strong>, <strong>sliced tomato</strong>, <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>, <strong>onion marmalade </strong>and <strong>ciabatta lids</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>cheesy garlic wedges </strong>and <strong>remaining shredded lettuce </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the shredded lettuce with the <strong>diced tomato</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
